<subSubSection pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1078,2042]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1258,1285]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Description</emphasis>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[396,491,1259,1285]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">holotype</typeStatus>
is 
<quantity box="[523,577,1259,1286]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="cm" value="8.0">8 cm</quantity>
high and 
<quantity box="[685,759,1258,1286]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="cm" value="8.5">8.5 cm</quantity>
wide, the stalk is 
<quantity box="[955,1029,1258,1286]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[1099,1194,1259,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 80" captionStartId="100.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@100.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURE 80. Litophyton type specimens: a, L. crassum (Kükenthal, 1903), NHMW C2370; b, L. capnelliformis (Thomson &amp; Dean, 1931), two parts of holotype ZMA COEL. 2925; c, L. darleyensis n. sp., holotype NTM C1155; d-e, L. folium n. sp., d, holotype NTM C4128; e, paratype NTM C10456. All natural size." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765091/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 80d</figureCitation>
). The polyps are up to 
<quantity box="[151,235,1295,1322]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
wide and high, grouped in conical catkins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1078,2042]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,276,1331,1357]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Polyps</emphasis>
. With irregular arrangement of sclerites in eight points (
<figureCitation box="[894,988,1330,1357]" captionStart="FIGURE 85" captionStartId="106.[151,248,1418,1443]" captionTargetBox="[158,1420,189,1384]" captionTargetId="figure@106.[151,1436,181,1393]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURE 85. Lateral views polyp armature of Litophyton species: a-b, L. folium n. sp., a, holotype NTM C4128, b, paratype NTM C10456; c, L. fusum n. sp., holotype NTM C4366; d; L. horseshoeensis, n. sp., holotype NTM C2256; e-f, L. sanctuaryensis n. sp., e, holotype NTM C1387; f, paratype NTM C4383; g. L. swainensis n. sp., holotype NTM C1371; h, L. verrucosum n. sp., holotype NTM C4071." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765101/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 85a</figureCitation>
). Abaxially and lateral point sclerites are spindles; abaxially up to 
<quantity box="[422,519,1367,1394]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
long, with spines and a few distal leaves (
<figureCitation box="[976,1070,1367,1394]" captionStart="FIGURE 86" captionStartId="107.[151,248,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@107.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURE 86. Litophyton folium n. sp., holotype NTM C4128; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, adaxial point spindles; c-d, tentacle rods and scales; e, supporting bundle spindles; f-g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h-i, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e, g, i; scale at b also applies to c, f, h." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765103" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765103/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 86a</figureCitation>
); laterally they are up to 
<quantity box="[1339,1436,1367,1394]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.20 mm</quantity>
long, with spines. Adaxially there are small, bent rods (
<figureCitation box="[770,866,1403,1430]" captionStart="FIGURE 86" captionStartId="107.[151,248,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@107.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURE 86. Litophyton folium n. sp., holotype NTM C4128; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, adaxial point spindles; c-d, tentacle rods and scales; e, supporting bundle spindles; f-g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h-i, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e, g, i; scale at b also applies to c, f, h." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765103" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765103/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 86b</figureCitation>
), up to 
<quantity box="[954,1053,1403,1430]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
long. The tentacles have rods and scales (
<figureCitation box="[231,310,1439,1466]" captionStart="FIGURE 86" captionStartId="107.[151,248,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@107.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURE 86. Litophyton folium n. sp., holotype NTM C4128; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, adaxial point spindles; c-d, tentacle rods and scales; e, supporting bundle spindles; f-g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h-i, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e, g, i; scale at b also applies to c, f, h." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765103" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765103/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
c-d). The polyp stalk has a few straight rods, up to 
<quantity box="[866,964,1439,1466]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
long (not depicted). Supporting bundle not projecting or slightly so, composed of spindles, up to 
<quantity box="[750,849,1475,1502]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.70 mm</quantity>
long, with simple tubercles and distally some spines (
<figureCitation box="[159,253,1511,1538]" captionStart="FIGURE 86" captionStartId="107.[151,248,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@107.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURE 86. Litophyton folium n. sp., holotype NTM C4128; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, adaxial point spindles; c-d, tentacle rods and scales; e, supporting bundle spindles; f-g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h-i, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e, g, i; scale at b also applies to c, f, h." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765103" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765103/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 86e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1078,2042]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1546,1573]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Surface layer top stalk</emphasis>
. Derivatives of capstans, 
<quantity box="[752,908,1546,1574]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.1" valueMax="0.15" valueMin="0.05">0.05-0.15 mm</quantity>
long; spindles and unilaterally spinose spindles are also present, up to 
<quantity box="[393,490,1582,1610]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.50 mm</quantity>
long, with simple and complex tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[950,1028,1583,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 86" captionStartId="107.[151,248,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@107.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURE 86. Litophyton folium n. sp., holotype NTM C4128; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, adaxial point spindles; c-d, tentacle rods and scales; e, supporting bundle spindles; f-g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h-i, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e, g, i; scale at b also applies to c, f, h." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765103" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765103/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
f-g). The unilaterally spinose sclerites have long spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1078,2042]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,482,1654,1681]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Surface layer base stalk</emphasis>
. Capstans, derivatives of capstans, spindles, and unilaterally spinose spindles, mostly with simple tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[405,485,1691,1718]" captionStart="FIGURE 86" captionStartId="107.[151,248,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@107.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURE 86. Litophyton folium n. sp., holotype NTM C4128; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, adaxial point spindles; c-d, tentacle rods and scales; e, supporting bundle spindles; f-g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h-i, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk. Scale at a also applies to e, g, i; scale at b also applies to c, f, h." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765103" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765103/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
h-i). The spines of the spinose sclerites are very long. Capstans 
<quantity box="[1215,1371,1690,1718]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.125" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.05">0.05-0.20 mm</quantity>
long; spindles up to about 
<quantity box="[376,473,1727,1754]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1078,2042]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1762,1789]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Interior stalk</emphasis>
. Spindles, up to 
<quantity box="[527,588,1763,1790]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long, with pointed ends (
<figureCitation box="[856,947,1763,1790]" captionStart="FIGURE 87" captionStartId="108.[151,248,1396,1421]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1370]" captionTargetId="figure@108.[164,1423,181,1370]" captionTargetPageId="108" captionText="FIGURE 87. Litophyton folium n. sp., holotype NTM C4128; a-b, spindles of interior base of stalk; c, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765105/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 87b</figureCitation>
) and simple and complex tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1424,1763,1790]" captionStart="FIGURE 87" captionStartId="108.[151,248,1396,1421]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1370]" captionTargetId="figure@108.[164,1423,181,1370]" captionTargetPageId="108" captionText="FIGURE 87. Litophyton folium n. sp., holotype NTM C4128; a-b, spindles of interior base of stalk; c, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765105/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig.87c</figureCitation>
); especially the smaller spindles with one or more side branches (
<figureCitation box="[844,938,1799,1825]" captionStart="FIGURE 87" captionStartId="108.[151,248,1396,1421]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1370]" captionTargetId="figure@108.[164,1423,181,1370]" captionTargetPageId="108" captionText="FIGURE 87. Litophyton folium n. sp., holotype NTM C4128; a-b, spindles of interior base of stalk; c, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765105" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765105/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 87a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,943,1835,1862]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1078,2042]" box="[199,943,1835,1862]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,1835,1861]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Etymology.</emphasis>
The Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[450,520,1835,1861]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="folium">
<emphasis box="[450,520,1835,1861]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">folium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, leaf, refers to the leafy point spindles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,873,1870,1898]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1078,2042]" box="[199,873,1870,1898]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,341,1870,1897]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Distribution</emphasis>
. Great Barrier Reef: Davies reef, Cockburn reef.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="102" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1078,2042]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,306,1907,1933]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Remarks</emphasis>
. NTM C4147, NTM C4386, and NTM 
<accessionNumber box="[746,833,1906,1933]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/C10456" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">C10456</accessionNumber>
(
<figureCitation box="[849,940,1907,1933]" captionStart="FIGURE 80" captionStartId="100.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@100.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="100" captionText="FIGURE 80. Litophyton type specimens: a, L. crassum (Kükenthal, 1903), NHMW C2370; b, L. capnelliformis (Thomson &amp; Dean, 1931), two parts of holotype ZMA COEL. 2925; c, L. darleyensis n. sp., holotype NTM C1155; d-e, L. folium n. sp., d, holotype NTM C4128; e, paratype NTM C10456. All natural size." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765091/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 80e</figureCitation>
) have slightly less developed polyp sclerites, seldom with distal leafy appearance (
<figureCitation box="[558,639,1943,1969]" captionStart="FIGURE 88" captionStartId="109.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@109.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURE 88. Litophyton folium n. sp., paratype NTM C10456; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c-d, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; e, polyp stalk rods; f, supporting bundle spindle; g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to f-i; scale at b also applies to c, e." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765107/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 88</figureCitation>
). The surface stalk sclerites of the base of NTM 
<accessionNumber box="[1188,1277,1942,1969]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/C10456" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">C10456</accessionNumber>
are less spiny (
<figureCitation box="[160,254,1979,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 88" captionStartId="109.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@109.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURE 88. Litophyton folium n. sp., paratype NTM C10456; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c-d, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; e, polyp stalk rods; f, supporting bundle spindle; g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to f-i; scale at b also applies to c, e." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765107/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 88h</figureCitation>
) and the internal stalk sclerites are shorter and less branched (
<figureCitation box="[940,1031,1979,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 88" captionStartId="109.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@109.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURE 88. Litophyton folium n. sp., paratype NTM C10456; a, abaxial point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c-d, adaxial and tentacle sclerites; e, polyp stalk rods; f, supporting bundle spindle; g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to f-i; scale at b also applies to c, e." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765107/files/figure.png" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Fig. 88j</figureCitation>
). Sclerite sampling of NTM 
<accessionNumber box="[1347,1437,1978,2005]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/C10456" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">C10456</accessionNumber>
was done somewhat above the base of the stalk, causing these differences.
</paragraph>
