<figureCitation box="[652,760,1721,1747]" captionStart="FIGURE 69" captionStartId="88.[151,248,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@88.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="FIGURE 69. Litophyton type specimens: a-c, L. brachiatum n. sp., a, holotype NTM C4154, b, paratype NTM C1473, c, paratype NTM C4179; d, L. bayeri (Verseveldt, 1966), syntypes RMNH 2239; e, L. debilis (Kükenthal, 1895) holotype SMF 64; f, L.burfordensis n. sp., holotype NTM C3171. All natural size." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765067/files/figure.png" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Figs. 69e</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[774,803,1722,1748]" captionStart="FIGURE 77" captionStartId="96.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,186,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@96.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="96" captionText="FIGURE 77. Litophyton debilis (Kükenthal, 1895), holotype SMF 64; a, lateral view polyp armature; b, abaxial view of polyp armature; c, abaxial point spindles; d, adaxial and tentacle scales; e, polyp stalk rods; f, supporting bundle spindle, partly; g, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk. Scale at f also applies to c, g-i; scale at d also applies to e." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765085" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765085/files/figure.png" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">77</figureCitation>
) resembles this species but has the larger interior stalk spindles also with side branches.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1436,1720,1964]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
The species also resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Van, 2020" authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[495,647,1793,1820]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="darleyensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[495,510,1794,1819]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[523,647,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">darleyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[652,735,1794,1820]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but has more developed point sclerites, more unilaterally spinose sclerites and shorter interior stalk spindles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1436,1720,1964]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
In group 
<collectionCode box="[298,317,1866,1892]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
also 
<taxonomicName authority="Van, 2020" authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[374,568,1866,1892]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="sanctuaryensis" status="sp. nov">
<emphasis box="[374,390,1866,1891]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[402,568,1866,1891]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">sanctuaryensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[575,653,1866,1892]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" rank="species">sp. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Van, 2020" authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[705,866,1866,1892]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="verrucosum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[705,721,1866,1891]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[734,866,1866,1891]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[872,956,1866,1892]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have unilaterally spinose sclerites with long spines. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[234,432,1902,1928]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="sanctuaryensis">
<emphasis box="[234,250,1902,1927]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[266,432,1902,1927]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">sanctuaryensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having much more robust interior stalk sclerites and the smaller ones are less branched. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van" authorityYear="2020" box="[268,429,1938,1964]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Litophyton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<emphasis box="[268,284,1938,1963]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[297,429,1938,1963]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has more robust interior stalk sclerites, which are not branched.
</paragraph>
